<br>
   I just basically suggested that they let the people keep failing to avoid problems and try another day.<br>
<br>
 I remember grouping once with 2 other Harmoniums and 3 AV's in BOT (fun group) and we failed a named because we were goofing off too much. Suddenly a group from another guild gave us 10 minutes to try again or they were taking over the camp. We laughed in their faces, but i think all of us were rather offended by it, and it played a part in my suggestion yesterday. <br>
<br>
3 or 4 hours is a lot longer than 10 minutes though, and I don't think that BC were the only ones waiting to have a shot at that spawn. Someone willing to keep at least  2 guilds from having a shot at a spawn for that long may be equally at fault. At any rate, i personally don't think it was a guildremove worthy offense. <br>
