<br>
We also took into consideration past behavior/attitude and actions.  This was not a matter of &lt;he said this&gt; &lt;I said that&gt; oh ok then we /guildremove.<br>
<br>
In the two years ive been with BC both as a member and officer I can count the number of people who officers guildremoved on one hand (this of course excludes trials and applicants.)  Dnot jump to the conclusion that we made this decision lightly.<br>
<br>
This thread is an apology from BloodCult to the Xev community for what happened in BoT on the 28th.  I believe in freedom of speech and the right to rant about any topic that comes to mind.  I do however ask that a new thread be made either to address the incident in BoT or the people that were removed.  Please leave this thread in the spirit with which it was made. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><br>
